observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
a. require the Municipal Treasurer/ Property Officer and Municipal Accountant to reconcile their respective PPE records to come up with reconciled balances of the PPE accounts to be presented in the financial statements; 
b. require the Inventory Committee to classify the PPE under Special Education Fund to their respective PPE account classification or category; 
c. avail of the One-Time Cleansing of PPE account balances provided in COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020, particularly applying the prescribed guidelines on the inventory, reconciliation of records and disposition for missing and unaccounted PPE.

observations.managementAction:
a. On a quarterly basis, inventory balances are now being prepared as basis for the recording of inventory;
b. Starting 2019, quarterly balances of inventories are now being recognized in the books of accounts;
c. Starting 2019, quarterly balances of inventories are now being forwarded to the accounting office, not just annual as basis.

observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
a. OIC-Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to analyze and reconcile the various discrepancies in balances of some PPE items between the accounting records and inventory reports and make the necessary adjustments and regularly reconcile the result of the physical count with the property and accounting records; 
b. OIC-Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to update and complete PPELCs and property records, respectively, of all property items by providing complete and necessary information on both records to facilitate verification and reconciliation.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Assessor to analyze and reconcile the discrepancy of P685,191,512.38 between the accounting and assessor’s records and make the necessary adjustments;
Municipal Accountant in coordination with the Municipal Assessor identify all the land owned by the Municipality to establish which are not yet recorded in the books;
Municipal Assessor to determine which real properties are not yet registered in the name of the Municipal Government to establish ownership over the land; and
Municipal Assessor and/or other concerned local officials facilitate the titling of real estate owned by the Municipality.
